originalText.text:
The Legend Malcolm X and his masjid, this was a really cool experience. It was one of my best memories and experiences reading Jummah at our beloved brothers masjid. The kutbha was delivered beautifully and gave me much insight to the troubles our brothers and sisters are facing here in the states. The masjid is big and spacious and it's a great space. Please do all go and pray there and fill this masjid up.
I recommend everyone go visit the masjid learn more about the history of Islam in the states.

originalText.text: Beautiful historic masjid. They need to appoint a more knowledgeable Imam. While listening to the khutbar, I wanted to walk out and find a masjid that adheres to Quran, Sunnah and the way of the first three generations. It’s not a good feeling to go to jummuah and feel like leaving because of the teachings not sticking to Quran and Sunnah. ESPECIALLY in such a historic masjid.

originalText.text:
As’Salamu’Alaykum!
This place is nice, looks regular masjid, person at the gate was very welcoming, and gave nice directions how to reach 3rd floor…By the time I was there, person preaching (Imam) and explaining good & bad and referring Quran in English and translating it, however not connecting whatsoever and no references from Hadiths either….most surprising thing is while praying Jummah prayer…he prayed super fast, I can’t even finish my Tasbih properly while at Ruku & Sujud!!
I don’t know, management should appoint someone more knowledgeable with Quran & Hadiths, who can give proper Jummah Khutba and know how to pray properly what we learned from our beloved prophet (SAW).
It’s a nice place to have middle of the Harlem, but need proper leaders to run this place!!
